\fs34 \cf0 \cb2 \strokec3 Let\'92s take a look at seven common cybersecurity frameworks and standards.\'a0\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf0 \cb2 \strokec3 The\'a0
\f0\b National Institute of Standards and Technology (NIST)
\f1\b0 \'a0is a non-regulatory US government agency dedicated to promoting American industrial competitiveness and innovation. NIST provides various resources and standards, including a framework for \'93Improving Critical Infrastructure cyber security,\'94 also known as the NIST cyber security framework.\'a0\
\
The\'a0
\f0\b International Standards Organization (ISO) 27001/27002
\f1\b0 \'a0framework is an internationally recognized standard for cyber security. With an ISO certification, organizations can demonstrate to the board, customers, partners, and shareholders that they are doing the right things with cyber risk management.\'a0\
\
The\'a0
\f0\b Center for Internet Security (CIS)
\f1\b0 \'a0is a nonprofit organization created by Eastern Europe and Asia countries. It focuses on improving cyber security readiness and response across the public and private sectors.\'a0\cb1 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f3 \cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1 \cf0 \cb2 \strokec3 The\'a0
\f0\b Service Organization Control (SOC) Type 2
\f1\b0 \'a0was developed by the American Institute of Certified Public Accountants (AICPA) to provide a trust-based cyber security framework and auditing standard. It helps verify that partners and vendors manage client data securely.\cb1 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f3 \cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1 \cf0 \cb2 \strokec3 The\'a0
\f0\b North American Electric Reliability Corporation\'97Critical Infrastructure Protection (NERC CIP)
\f1\b0 \'a0provides a set of cyber security standards for the utility and power sectors. NERC CIP was created in response to the rise in attacks on critical US infrastructure and increasing third-party risks. It aims to help reduce cyber risk and maintain the reliability of bulk electric systems.\cb1 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f3 \cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

