\fs64 \cf0 \cb2 \strokec3 Cybersecurity Threat Landscape\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa408\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs40\fsmilli20400 \cf0 \cb2 \strokec3 Cybersecurity Threats
\f1\b0 \'a0refer to any potential danger that may result from unauthorized access to computer systems or networks, data theft, or other malicious activities aimed at exploiting vulnerabilities in a digital infrastructure.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \cb2 \strokec3 The\'a0
\f0\b \cb2 \strokec3 Cybersecurity\'a0Threat Landscape
\f1\b0 \cb2 \strokec3 \'a0is the entirety of potential and identified cyberthreats affecting a particular sector, group of users, time period, and so forth.\'a0\

\f0\b\fs36 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF65539 \cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs34 \AppleTypeServices \cf0 \cb2 \strokec3 The threat landscape is constantly evolving and new threats are emerging all the time. To stay ahead of these threats, cybersecurity professionals must stay up-to-date on the latest trends. They should be proactive in their efforts to protect their organizations from cyberattacks. They keep implementing robust security measures, regularly testing and updating those measures, and educating their employees on best practices for cybersecurity hygiene.\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\qc\partightenfactor0

\fs76\fsmilli38400 \cf0 \cb2 \strokec3 Attack Vectors\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs40\fsmilli20400 \cf0 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa816\partightenfactor0

\f0\b \cf0 \cb2 \strokec3 Attack Vectors\'a0
\f1\b0 \cb2 \strokec3 are methods or mechanisms cybercriminals use to gain illegal, unauthorized access to computer systems and networks. The motivations for using cybersecurity threat vectors vary by the type of attacker. \'a0\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \cb2 The most common types of attack vectors include the following:\cb1 \
Sooftware Vulnerabilities: 
\fs32 \cb2 \strokec3 If a computer system, network, operating system, or application has an unpatched security vulnerability, an attacker can use a threat vector to gain unauthorized access.\cb1 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f3 \cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1 \cf0 \cb2 \strokec3 Compromised credentials are the most-used attack vector as people continue to use weak passwords to protect their online accounts and profiles. Compromised credentials occur when information like usernames or passwords are exposed to a third party such as mobile apps and websites.\'a0\
\
Cyber criminals focus their efforts on hacking user IDs and passwords that are weak or can be easily guessed. They also steal credentials by using programs that monitor public Wi-Fi networks for when users input their access credentials.\'a0\cb1 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f3 \cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1 \cf0 \cb2 \strokec3 Malicious employees are the employees who exposes their company information and exploits company vulnerabilities. They are often unhappy employees. Users with access to sensitive data and networks can inflict extensive damage through privileged misuse and malicious intent.\'a0\
\
Encryption is a method of hiding the true meaning of a message and protects digital data by converting it into a code or ciphertext. This ensures that the data within a message cannot be read by an unauthorized party, which helps prevent cyber criminals from stealing sensitive information.\
\
Missing, poor, or weak encryption leads to the transmission of sensitive data in plaintext. This risks its exposure to unauthorized parties if intercepted or obtained through a brute-force attack.\'a0\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF65539 \cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs32 \AppleTypeServices \cf0 \cb2 \strokec3 One of the most common attack vectors, email attachments can contain malicious code that executes after a user opens the file. In recent years, many cyber criminals have used this threat vector.\cb1 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f3 \cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1 \cf0 \cb2 \strokec3 In many cases, companies entrust their security to outside system and network vendors, cloud providers, and business partners. When the systems of these third parties are breached, the information obtain by cyber criminals may also contain sensitive information from the companies.\cb1 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f3 \cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1 \cf0 \cb2 \strokec3 Instead of going after user accounts directly, an attacker may aim to infect a trusted third-party application with malware. They can also create a fake, malicious application that users unknowingly download and install. This is a common attack vector for mobile devices.\cb1 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

