\f0\b \cf0 \cb2 \strokec3 SQL Injection
\f1\b0 \cb2 \strokec3 \'a0is a code injection technique that is used to attack data-driven applications, in which malicious SQL statements are inserted into an entry field for execution.\'a0\cb1 \
\cb2 In an SQL injection attack, the attacker must exploit a security vulnerability in an application's software. For example, when user input is either incorrectly filtered for string literal escape characters embedded in SQL statements or user input is not strongly typed and unexpectedly executed.\'a0\cb1 \
\cb2 SQL Injection is mostly known as an attack vector for websites but can be used to attack any type of SQL database.\cb1 \
