\f0\b \cf0 \cb2 \strokec3 Dwell Time
\f1\b0 \'a0in cybersecurity refers to the duration a cyber threat remains undetected within a computer network or system. It is the time between when an attacker gains unauthorized access to a network or system and when the attack is finally detected and neutralized.\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa408\partightenfactor0

\fs40\fsmilli20400 \cf0 \cb2 \strokec3 Dwell time can vary greatly depending on the complexity of the attack and the security measures that are in place to detect it. In some cases, attackers can remain undetected for months or even years, allowing them to gather sensitive information or cause significant damage to the network or system.\cb1 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \cb2 \strokec3 Reducing dwell time is an important part of effective cybersecurity measures. The longer an attacker remains undetected, the more damage they can do to the organization.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2 \cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

