\f1 \cf0 \cb2 Some important cyber safety measures are listed below.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf0 \cb2 \strokec3 A\'a0
\f0\b Network Firewall
\f1\b0 \'a0is a barricade that resides between an internal network and the public Internet. The main purpose of a firewall is to allow non-threatening traffic in and to keep unsafe traffic out.\cb1 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f3 \cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1 \cf0 \cb2 \strokec3 An\'a0
\f0\b Antivirus Software
\f1\b0 \'a0is a set of programs that are intended to prevent, detect, and remove viruses and other malicious software like worms, trojans, spyware, and more.\'a0\cb1 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f3 \cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1 \cf0 \cb2 \strokec3 An\'a0
\f0\b Intrusion Prevention System (IPS)
\f1\b0 \'a0is a network security tool that monitors network or system activities for malicious activity. Key functions of IPSs are to identify malicious activity, collect information about this activity, report it, and attempt to block or stop it.\'a0\cb1 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f3 \cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1 \cf0 \cb2 \strokec3 A\'a0
\f0\b Vulnerability Management Tool
\f1\b0 \'a0is used to scan networks, computing systems, and software programs for exploitable weaknesses. Upon detection of weaknesses, the tool either suggests or initiates remediation actions. This tool reduces the potential for a successful cyberattack.\cb1 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f3 \cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b \cf0 \cb2 \strokec3 Web Application and API Protection (WAAP)
\f1\b0 \'a0is a class of security technologies designed to protects web applications by filtering and monitoring HTTP and API traffic between a web application and the Internet. It protects your applications and APIs against threats and fraud and ensures availability and compliance.\cb1 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f3 \cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b \cf0 \cb2 \strokec3 Browser Isolation
\f1\b0 , also known as Web Isolation, is a technology that contains web browsing activity inside an isolated environment in order to protect computers from any malware the user may encounter. This isolation may occur locally on the computer or remotely on a server.\cb1 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f3 \cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1 \cf0 \cb2 \strokec3 A\'a0
\f0\b Sandbox\'a0
\f1\b0 is a security technique that is used to restrict the interaction of a program with the operating system simply because the program is untested, or the program contains some malicious codes. This is usually done while analyzing or testing a program such as new software or malware.\cb1 \strokec3 \
